        "name": "How long should a resume be?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "For most professionals, one page is ideal. Senior executives with 15+ years of experience can use two pages. Never exceed two pages. Recruiters spend an average of 7 seconds scanning a resume."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What resume format is best for ATS?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The hybrid (combination) format works best for most ATS systems. Use standard section headings, avoid tables and columns, include relevant keywords from the job description, and submit as a DOCX file."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Should I include a cover letter?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Yes â€ 83% of hiring managers say cover letters influence their decisions. Tailor each cover letter to the specific role, highlight your relevant achievements, and explain why you're interested in the company."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>

